🟠 Medium — Server DELETE_DATA Loses RF Resolution Setting
gprs_core.ino line 513 — LCD factory reset preserves station.txt, rf_fw.txt, station.doc, and rf_res.txt. Server-triggered DELETE_DATA preserves only the first three — rf_res.txt is deleted. On next boot, rf_fw.txt still equals DEFAULT_RF_RESOLUTION, so no firmware-change is detected, and rf_res.txt is recreated at DEFAULT_RF_RESOLUTION = 0.50. If a unit was field-calibrated to 0.25mm, all subsequent rainfall is double-counted with no error indication.
